---
description: Stylesheet house conventions - apply when editing SCSS/CSS files in an Angular workspace.
globs: "**/*.scss,**/*.css"
alwaysApply: false
---

When creating or editing stylesheets (`.scss`, `.css`) in an Angular workspace, follow the
house styling conventions carried by the `angular-styling` skill installed under
`.cursor/skills/`: encapsulation choices, `:host`, design tokens as CSS custom properties,
and a mobile-first breakpoint approach. Prefer these over ad-hoc style.

If the `angular-styling` skill is not loaded, hold the line on the highest-value rules:
prefer `:host`/component encapsulation over global overrides, express design tokens as CSS
custom properties rather than hard-coded values, write mobile-first (base styles unqualified,
breakpoints as min-width overrides), and never reach for `::ng-deep` without the skill's
sanctioned escape hatch.

This is guidance, auto-attached whenever a `.scss` or `.css` file is in context (not a hard
block).
